usdBgpMIB.name: usdBgpMIB

revisions.description: Added support for BGP internal redistribute. Obsoleted usdBgpStorageInitialHistoryRoutePoolSize and usdBgpStorageMaxHistoryRoutePoolSize. Added the ability to unconfigure BGP attributes from the MIB.
Added support for adding unicast BGP routes into a multicast view.
Added support for peer and peer-group local-as.

Replaced the route tables to add original route destination as an index: usdBgpRouteTable > usdBgpNewRouteTable usdBgpRouteFlapHistoryTable > usdBgpNewRouteFlapHistoryTable usdBgpRouteCommunityTable > usdBgpNewRouteCommunityTable usdBgpRouteExtendedCommunityTable > usdBgpNewRouteExtendedCommunityTable usdBgpRouteClusterIdTable > usdBgpNewRouteClusterIdTable
Added support for BGP default IPv4 unicast.
Redesigned version of this MIB module.
Initial version of this MIB module.

UsdBgpStorageInteger.name: UsdBgpStorageInteger
UsdBgpStorageInteger.description: Specifies an unsigned integer. If an object with this type is set while BGP is created, the value will not be used until a reboot occurs.

UsdBgpResetConnectionType.name: UsdBgpResetConnectionType
UsdBgpResetConnectionType.description: Writing a value to an object of this type will cause the corresponding reset action to take place: resetTypeNoop - no action (this value is always returned on a read) resetTypeHard - causes a BGP session to be dropped and then re-established resetTypeSoftIn - causes inbound policy to be re-applied to received routes resetTypeSoftOut - causes outbound policy to be re-applied to sent routes resetTypeSoftInOut - does both resetTypeSoftIn and resetTypeSoftOut resetTypeRouteFlapHistory - causes route-flap dampening history to be discarded

usdBgpLocalAsNumber.name: usdBgpLocalAsNumber
usdBgpLocalAsNumber.description: The local autonomous system number. This object cannot be modified if BGP is enabled.

usdBgpEnabled.name: usdBgpEnabled
usdBgpEnabled.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have BGP router enabled.

usdBgpIdentifier.name: usdBgpIdentifier
usdBgpIdentifier.description: The BGP identifier of the local system. The identifier is the system router ID by default.

usdBgpAlwaysCompareMed.name: usdBgpAlwaysCompareMed
usdBgpAlwaysCompareMed.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to compare metrics for paths from neighors of different ASs.

usdBgpEqualCostLimit.name: usdBgpEqualCostLimit
usdBgpEqualCostLimit.description: The maximum equal cost paths to store in routing table.

usdBgpClientToClientReflection.name: usdBgpClientToClientReflection
usdBgpClientToClientReflection.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have client-to-client route reflection enabled.

usdBgpClusterId.name: usdBgpClusterId
usdBgpClusterId.description: The cluster ID. When this object is zero, the router ID will be used.

usdBgpConfederationId.name: usdBgpConfederationId
usdBgpConfederationId.description: The confederation ID. When this object is zero, the router is not in a confederation.

usdBgpMissingAsWorst.name: usdBgpMissingAsWorst
usdBgpMissingAsWorst.description: If this object is set to true(1) routes without a MED attribute are considered worse than routes with a MED attribute. If this object is set to false(0) routes without a MED attribute are considered better than routes with a MED attribute.

usdBgpResetAllConnectionType.name: usdBgpResetAllConnectionType
usdBgpResetAllConnectionType.description: Writing a value to this object causes all sessions to all peers to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). Reading this object has no effect and always returns resetTypeNoop.

usdBgpAdvertiseInactive.name: usdBgpAdvertiseInactive
usdBgpAdvertiseInactive.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to propagate received BGP routes which are not the best route in the IP forwarding table.

usdBgpEnforceFirstAs.name: usdBgpEnforceFirstAs
usdBgpEnforceFirstAs.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to check whether the first AS number in the AS-path in routes from EBGP peers is consistent with the AS number of the peer.

usdBgpConfedCompareMed.name: usdBgpConfedCompareMed
usdBgpConfedCompareMed.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to compare metrics for paths from neighors of different sub-ASs in the same confederation.

usdBgpGlobalRetryInterval.name: usdBgpGlobalRetryInterval
usdBgpGlobalRetryInterval.description: The default number of seconds before BGP retries to establish an outgoing BGP session.

usdBgpGlobalConfigKeepAliveInterval.name: usdBgpGlobalConfigKeepAliveInterval
usdBgpGlobalConfigKeepAliveInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer for all peers. Zero means don't send KeepAlive messages.

usdBgpGlobalConfigHoldTime.name: usdBgpGlobalConfigHoldTime
usdBgpGlobalConfigHoldTime.description: Default time interval in seconds for the Hold timer for all peers. Zero means don't expect KeepAlive message to be received.

usdBgpGlobalAsOriginationInterval.name: usdBgpGlobalAsOriginationInterval
usdBgpGlobalAsOriginationInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer for all peers.

usdBgpExternalAdvertisementInterval.name: usdBgpExternalAdvertisementInterval
usdBgpExternalAdvertisementInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer for all external peers.

usdBgpGlobalRibOutEnabled.name: usdBgpGlobalRibOutEnabled
usdBgpGlobalRibOutEnabled.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to enable RIB-out by default for all peers, or to false(2) to disable RIB-out by default for all peers.

usdBgpOverloadShutdown.name: usdBgpOverloadShutdown
usdBgpOverloadShutdown.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to shut itself down when it runs out of memory. Set this object to false(2) for BGP to continue running (with incomplete information) when it runs out of memory.

usdBgpLogNeighborChanges.name: usdBgpLogNeighborChanges
usdBgpLogNeighborChanges.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP log a message whenever a peer enters or leaves the established state.

usdBgpFastExternalFallover.name: usdBgpFastExternalFallover
usdBgpFastExternalFallover.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to immediately bring down any directly adjacent EBGP session on a link down.

usdBgpInternalAdvertisementInterval.name: usdBgpInternalAdvertisementInterval
usdBgpInternalAdvertisementInterval.description: Default time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer for all internal peers.

usdBgpMaxAsLimit.name: usdBgpMaxAsLimit
usdBgpMaxAsLimit.description: Maximum length of received AS-path. Received routes with an AS-path longer than this are not placed in the IP forwarding table and are not propagated to other peers. Zero means no maximum length.

usdBgpPreviousOperationalState.name: usdBgpPreviousOperationalState
usdBgpPreviousOperationalState.description: The BGP instance previous operational state.

usdBgpAutomaticRouteTargetFilter.name: usdBgpAutomaticRouteTargetFilter
usdBgpAutomaticRouteTargetFilter.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to enable automatic route-target filtering.

usdBgpDefaultIPv4Unicast.name: usdBgpDefaultIPv4Unicast
usdBgpDefaultIPv4Unicast.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to automatically activate peers in the IPv4 unicast address family.

usdBgpRedistributeInternal.name: usdBgpRedistributeInternal
usdBgpRedistributeInternal.description: Set this object to true(1) for BGP to automatically redistribute iBGP routes to IGP protocols.

usdBgpUnconfiguredAttributes.name: usdBgpUnconfiguredAttributes
usdBgpUnconfiguredAttributes.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured. On write each bit indicates wheter or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. Setting an attribute to a value has the automatic side-effect of setting the bit with the same name to zero.

usdBgpBaselineTime.name: usdBgpBaselineTime
usdBgpBaselineTime.description: The sysUpTime at which the counters were most recently baselined.

usdBgpDestinationMemoryUsed.name: usdBgpDestinationMemoryUsed

usdBgpRouteMemoryUsed.name: usdBgpRouteMemoryUsed

usdBgpSelectedRouteCount.name: usdBgpSelectedRouteCount

usdBgpPathAttributeCount.name: usdBgpPathAttributeCount

usdBgpPathAttributeMemoryUsed.name: usdBgpPathAttributeMemoryUsed

usdBgpPeerAdminStatus.name: usdBgpPeerAdminStatus
usdBgpPeerAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the BGP connection. A transition from 'stop' to 'start' will cause the BGP Start Event to be generated. A transition from 'start' to 'stop' will cause the BGP Stop Event to be generated. This parameter can be used to restart BGP peer connections. Care should be used in providing write access to this object without adequate authentication.

usdBgpPeerLocalAddressMask.name: usdBgpPeerLocalAddressMask
usdBgpPeerLocalAddressMask.description: The local IP address mask of this entry's BGP connection.

usdBgpPeerLocalPort.name: usdBgpPeerLocalPort
usdBgpPeerLocalPort.description: The local port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers.

usdBgpPeerRemotePort.name: usdBgpPeerRemotePort
usdBgpPeerRemotePort.description: The remote port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers. Note that the objects bgpPeerLocalAddr, bgpPeerLocalPort, bgpPeerRemoteAddr and bgpPeerRemotePort provide the appropriate reference to the standard MIB TCP connection table.

usdBgpPeerInUpdates.name: usdBgpPeerInUpdates
usdBgpPeerInUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

usdBgpPeerOutUpdates.name: usdBgpPeerOutUpdates
usdBgpPeerOutUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages transmitted on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

usdBgpPeerInTotalMessages.name: usdBgpPeerInTotalMessages
usdBgpPeerInTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages received from the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

usdBgpPeerOutTotalMessages.name: usdBgpPeerOutTotalMessages
usdBgpPeerOutTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages transmitted to the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

usdBgpPeerLastErrorCode.name: usdBgpPeerLastErrorCode
usdBgpPeerLastErrorCode.description: The last error code and subcode seen by this peer on this connection. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the error code, and the second byte contains the subcode.

usdBgpPeerLastResetReason.name: usdBgpPeerLastResetReason
usdBgpPeerLastResetReason.description: The string representing the last error code seen by this peer on this connection. If no error has occurred, this string is null.

usdBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.name: usdBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions
usdBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.description: The total number of times the BGP FSM transitioned into the established state.

usdBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.name: usdBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTime
usdBgpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.description: This timer indicates how long (in seconds) this peer has been in the Established state or how long since this peer was last in the Established state. It is set to zero when a new peer is configured or the router is booted.

usdBgpPeerRetryInterval.name: usdBgpPeerRetryInterval
usdBgpPeerRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

usdBgpPeerHoldTime.name: usdBgpPeerHoldTime
usdBgpPeerHoldTime.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker by using the smaller of the value in bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured and the Hold Time received in the OPEN message. This value must be at lease three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Timer has not been established with the peer, or, the value of bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured is zero (0).

usdBgpPeerKeepAliveInterval.name: usdBgpPeerKeepAliveInterval
usdBgpPeerKeepAliveInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker such that, when compared with bgpPeerHoldTime, it has the same proportion as what bgpPeerKeepAliveConfigured has when compared with bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), it indicates that the KeepAlive timer has not been established with the peer, or, the value of bgpPeerKeepAliveConfigured is zero (0).

usdBgpPeerConfigHoldTime.name: usdBgpPeerConfigHoldTime
usdBgpPeerConfigHoldTime.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (bgpPeerHoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be established with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

usdBgpPeerConfigKeepAliveInterval.name: usdBgpPeerConfigKeepAliveInterval
usdBgpPeerConfigKeepAliveInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages' frequency relative to the value specified in bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by bgpPeerKeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of bgpPeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

usdBgpPeerAsOriginationInterval.name: usdBgpPeerAsOriginationInterval
usdBgpPeerAsOriginationInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 10 seconds.

usdBgpPeerAdvertisementInterval.name: usdBgpPeerAdvertisementInterval
usdBgpPeerAdvertisementInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

usdBgpPeerInUpdateElapsedTime.name: usdBgpPeerInUpdateElapsedTime
usdBgpPeerInUpdateElapsedTime.description: Elapsed time in seconds since the last BGP UPDATE message was received from the peer. Each time bgpPeerInUpdates is incremented, the value of this object is set to zero (0).

usdBgpPeerWeight.name: usdBgpPeerWeight
usdBgpPeerWeight.description: The weight assigned to routes learned from peer.

usdBgpPeerEbgpMultihopTtl.name: usdBgpPeerEbgpMultihopTtl
usdBgpPeerEbgpMultihopTtl.description: Maximum number of hops to the external peer (only relevant if EBGP multihop turned on).

usdBgpPeerUpdateSource.name: usdBgpPeerUpdateSource
usdBgpPeerUpdateSource.description: The source IP address for peer connections.

usdBgpPeerMd5Password.name: usdBgpPeerMd5Password
usdBgpPeerMd5Password.description: The password for MD5 authentication. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

usdBgpPeerMaxUpdateSize.name: usdBgpPeerMaxUpdateSize
usdBgpPeerMaxUpdateSize.description: The maximum size in bytes of transmitted UPDATE messages.

usdBgpPeerCapabilityMultiProtocol.name: usdBgpPeerCapabilityMultiProtocol
usdBgpPeerCapabilityMultiProtocol.description: The peer supports the multi-protocol capablity.

usdBgpPeerCapabilityRouteRefresh.name: usdBgpPeerCapabilityRouteRefresh

usdBgpPeerCapabilityRouteRefreshCiscoPro.name: usdBgpPeerCapabilityRouteRefreshCiscoProprietary
usdBgpPeerCapabilityRouteRefreshCiscoPro.description: The peer supports the route-refresh-cisco capability.

usdBgpPeerResetConnectionType.description: Writing a value to this object causes the session to the peer to be cleared; the value determines what type of clear is executed (hard clear, soft clear in, soft clear out, etc.). Reading this object has no effect and always returns resetTypeNoop.

usdBgpPeerLocalAsNumber.description: The local autonomous system number to be used for this peer. Value zero (0) means that the global local automous system number (as specified in the object usdBgpLocalAsNumber) is used.

usdBgpPeerUnconfiguredAttributes.name: usdBgpPeerUnconfiguredAttributes
usdBgpPeerUnconfiguredAttributes.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured. On write each bit indicates wheter or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. usdBgpAddressFamilyUnconfiguredAttribute.name: usdBgpAddressFamilyUnconfiguredAttributes
usdBgpAddressFamilyUnconfiguredAttribute.description: On get each bit indicates whether the corresponding attribute is configured or unconfigured: 0 = The attribute is configured (i.e. the configured value is the operational value). 1 = The attribute is unconfigured (i.e. the operational value is inherited from the a higher level which could be the default value). Getting the attribute value itself always returns the operational value of that attribute regardless of whether the attribute is configured or unconfigured. On write each bit indicates wheter or not the corresponding attribute should be set to the unconfigured state: 0 = No operation (i.e. do not change the state of the attribute). 1 = Set the attribute to the unconfigured state. Setting an attribute to a value has the automatic side-effect of setting the bit with the same name to zero.
